 Corrective Maintenance;   When errors or bugs are found withing a system they need to be corrected    Adaptive Maintenance;
 Systems need to adapt to changes. Could be changes to internal procedures within an org or other external changes. Enables and Org to comply with new laws.    Perfective Maintenance;
 To always looking to improve system, even is there is nothing wrong with it. Ideas to make the system perform better or to do additional tasks.    Preventative Maintenance
 Required to prevent problems arising withing a system. Apply to both hardware and software. Hardware should be regularly cleaned. Regular scans of storage media
